Title: Chief Culture Officer
Q48 (Workplace Health Assessment): There's a strong sense of informal leadership that isn't always recognized in official structures.
Q49 (Strengths/Barriers): We excel at client delivery due to dedicated staff. Our biggest barrier is resistance to adopting new technologies internally.
Q50 (Workplace Improvement): Encourage more cross-functional collaboration and reduce departmental silos.

Title: Sr. Director
Q48 (Workplace Health Assessment): Recent mergers have created some cultural integration challenges, especially between older and newer teams.
Q49 (Strengths/Barriers): Our team's agility and adaptability are key strengths. The biggest barrier is a lack of consistent, constructive feedback.
Q50 (Workplace Improvement): Provide training on effective conflict resolution and 'tough conversations' to improve team dynamics.

Title: Head of People and Culture
Q48 (Workplace Health Assessment): A lot of change fatigue is present due to frequent restructuring initiatives.
Q49 (Strengths/Barriers): Our team's agility and adaptability are key strengths. The biggest barrier is a lack of consistent, constructive feedback.

Title: Director
Q48 (Workplace Health Assessment): There's an unwritten rule about not challenging senior management, which stifles innovation.
Q49 (Strengths/Barriers): Strengths include our collaborative spirit and dedication; barriers are decision-making bottlenecks and lack of cross-departmental understanding.
Q50 (Workplace Improvement): More transparent communication from leadership, especially regarding strategic decisions.
